  <section id="background">
    <h2 class="font-pixel text-[10px] text-arcade-cyan mb-4 leading-loose">// Background</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-arcade-text mb-4">
     I'm a Software Engineer turned engineering leader with nearly three decades in the industry, most recently serving
     as a Director. My career has been deeply rooted in open-source and Linux, and while I love building strong teams
     and coaching the next generation of engineering leaders, I'm still very much hands-on, whether that's writing code,
     diving into architecture, or getting into the technical weeds with my team. This follows me home, where I run
     OpenHAB for home automation and OpenWRT to keep my network exactly the way I like it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-arcade-text mb-4">
     Outside of work, I stay busy with a mix of hobbies that keep things interesting. I'm an avid cyclist and occasional
     runner, and I love getting lost in a good science fiction novel or the latest DC Comics run. You might also find me
     building LEGO, playing board games with friends and family, watching movies, or outside somewhere, camera in tow,
     looking for something worth framing. (Lately, though, an embarrassing amount of my free time has been claimed by
     Slay the Spire II.) I'm also a craft beer enthusiast, always happy to discover what's new from a local brewery. I
     also volunteer with Scouting America where it turns out I develop leaders for free too.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-arcade-text">
     My wife Sarah and I have been married 24 years, and together we've raised two kids we're incredibly proud of:
     Dinah, a fourth-year at her parents' alma mater, the University of Illinois, and Evan, a freshman at Marquette.
     When we get a moment to ourselves, you'll likely find us exploring a new winery or sharing a good bottle at home.
    </p>
  </section>

